00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:31,452
''But something sure
stirred in my heart''

111
00:17:04,456 --> 00:17:10,918
''The cascade of my hair
is filled with sweet fragrance''

112
00:17:19,304 --> 00:17:21,932
''Doors open to reveal secret longings;

113
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:25,777
''something stirred in my heart''

114
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:29,775
''Who knows what you said''

115
00:17:30,649 --> 00:17:33,447
''Who knows what l heard''

116
00:17:34,319 --> 00:17:36,947
''Something stirred in my heart''

117
00:18:03,282 --> 00:18:05,250
Excuse me...
- Yes?

118
00:18:07,453 --> 00:18:10,422
That song you were singing...
- You like it?

119
00:18:11,123 --> 00:18:13,091
Where did you get it?

120
00:18:14,626 --> 00:18:16,093
lt's mine.

121
00:18:17,463 --> 00:18:20,591
lt isn't yours.
- Then why ask, if you know?

122
00:18:20,799 --> 00:18:24,929
Because l <i>....</i>
- What do you want?

123
00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:29,604
The file with that song in it.

124
00:18:29,808 --> 00:18:31,776
ls that all?

125
00:18:32,644 --> 00:18:34,612
l don't like prattle.

126
00:18:36,982 --> 00:18:38,950
Do you like me?

127
00:18:40,486 --> 00:18:41,953
No.

128
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:45,116
Then why follow me?

129
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:47,792
l want to know only that the
file is with you or not.

130
00:18:47,993 --> 00:18:50,461
lt's valuable to me.
Whenever l have money...

131
00:18:50,996 --> 00:18:56,798
So you've followed
me empty-handed? Get out!

132
00:18:57,336 --> 00:18:59,964
Please understand.
l want only that file.

133
00:19:00,339 --> 00:19:01,636
For me it is important.

134
00:19:01,773 --> 00:19:05,641
You go, or should l
remove my sandal.

135
00:19:14,186 --> 00:19:17,815
Stop shouting, silly.
Your customer will run away.

136
00:19:18,023 --> 00:19:21,982
A pauper! l lured him here,
but he hasn't a penny.

137
00:19:45,717 --> 00:19:47,685
Juhi, it was him.

138
00:19:48,887 --> 00:19:52,345
Gulabo, where are you running?

139
00:19:53,058 --> 00:19:56,619
l must apologize to him,
l treated him very badly.

140
00:20:07,839 --> 00:20:13,141
Stop talking in riddles
and tell me in plain words.

141
00:20:14,012 --> 00:20:16,310
What's all this about?

142
00:20:18,016 --> 00:20:21,315
The man who followed me
is a poet.

143
00:20:22,688 --> 00:20:26,488
The poet whose poems l bought
as waste paper.

144
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:30,487
Look: the same paper,
the same writing.

145
00:20:31,196 --> 00:20:33,994
And l threw him out as a pauper.

146
00:20:36,034 --> 00:20:42,837
He is a pauper.
You did quite the right thing.

147
00:20:43,542 --> 00:20:48,502
Foolish girl! Come on

148
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:09,127
Have you written any poems
in the holidays?

149
00:22:09,494 --> 00:22:11,291
A few.

150
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:17,298
Anyone can write poems. lf you're
a true poet, create something.

151
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:19,637
Extempore?

152
00:22:25,577 --> 00:22:27,545
But on what subject?

153
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:32,983
Who is she?

154
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:37,986
There's your subject:
a poem about her.

155
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:45,986
''When l walk,
even my shadow lags behind''

156
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:53,937
''When you walk,
the universe keeps pace''

157
00:22:55,474 --> 00:22:59,274
''When l stop,
clouds of misery gather''

158
00:23:00,812 --> 00:23:04,441
''When you stop...
spring's radiance is outshone''

159
00:23:38,517 --> 00:23:39,984
Miss Pushlata.

160
00:25:25,490 --> 00:25:31,451
''Our love will survive every trial''

161
00:25:35,767 --> 00:25:41,467
''We shall never forget
our oath of love''

162
00:25:56,454 --> 00:26:02,586
''We leave the world
far behind''

163
00:26:03,295 --> 00:26:08,597
''How long will we
journey together?''

164
00:26:59,618 --> 00:27:00,585
Coolie!

165
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:12,752
A coolie.
- At your service.

166
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:19,262
Put these in the car.

167
00:27:24,142 --> 00:27:27,111
What has the world come to?

168
00:27:27,312 --> 00:27:29,439
The educated work as coolies.

169
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,618
Have your money.

170
00:28:01,279 --> 00:28:04,248
No credit.

171
00:28:16,461 --> 00:28:18,429
lt's counterfeit.

172
00:28:28,139 --> 00:28:30,437
So you've got nothing else.

173
00:28:32,811 --> 00:28:35,780
So that's your game!

174
00:28:36,481 --> 00:28:38,779
Now who'll pay for that food
you've touched?

175
00:28:39,084 --> 00:28:41,780
Pay up, or l'll have your shirt.

176
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,947
Take the plate away.

177
00:28:44,656 --> 00:28:46,624
Put it back!

178
00:28:49,327 --> 00:28:51,295
Keep the change.

179
00:28:51,996 --> 00:28:56,456
Go to a barber and get yourself
made to look more human.

180
00:29:04,843 --> 00:29:06,310
Do eat.

181
00:29:10,348 --> 00:29:13,977
l'm not hungry.
- Yes, you are.

182
00:29:14,686 --> 00:29:16,654
You've no right to take pity on me.

183
00:29:24,696 --> 00:29:26,323
l'm sorry...

184
00:29:28,533 --> 00:29:30,501
...take no notice of me.

185
00:29:31,369 --> 00:29:34,338
You have every right
to be angry.

186
00:29:35,373 --> 00:29:39,002
l treated you very badly
the other day.

187
00:29:41,045 --> 00:29:42,512
l've nothing against you.

188
00:29:44,215 --> 00:29:46,183
Then please eat...

189
00:29:47,719 --> 00:29:48,686
...for my sake.

190
00:29:51,389 --> 00:29:54,449
What did you say?
For your sake?

191
00:29:55,994 --> 00:29:59,293
You don't even know me.

192
00:30:00,331 --> 00:30:02,959
l know you very well.
- How?

193
00:30:04,002 --> 00:30:05,970
Through your poems.

194
00:30:07,672 --> 00:30:09,799
l know your thoughts
and feelings.

195
00:30:10,508 --> 00:30:12,476
What else is there?

196
00:30:14,679 --> 00:30:16,647
l don't understand.

197
00:30:21,019 --> 00:30:22,316
But, Miss...

198
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:24,488
Why address me so politely?

199
00:30:26,357 --> 00:30:28,325
l am not used to it.

200
00:30:31,362 --> 00:30:35,822
Until today, people
have spoken rudely to me.

201
00:30:37,368 --> 00:30:40,826
l have suffered
their vulgar remarks...

202
00:30:42,207 --> 00:30:45,665
...their abuse, their crude jokes.

203
00:30:46,878 --> 00:30:50,837
But you behave so respectfully.

204
