''lf your head reels with pain,
or your heart sinks in gloom...''

221
00:35:33,664 --> 00:35:38,465
''Don't fret, leave it to me;
l'll set things right soon''

222
00:35:41,672 --> 00:35:43,799
Mr. Vijay, come here!

223
00:35:44,242 --> 00:35:48,474
A great poet: l was singing
one of his songs.

224
00:35:49,013 --> 00:35:54,076
Since l've been singing your
song, business has doubled.

225
00:35:55,286 --> 00:35:56,753
Don't go

226
00:35:57,054 --> 00:35:59,249
l'll just finish him.
- What?

227
00:35:59,624 --> 00:36:00,921
Stay put.

228
00:36:01,125 --> 00:36:05,755
Mr. Vijay, l'll give you a
special massage completely free.

229
00:36:06,797 --> 00:36:13,100
No, thank you. The present
times have battered me enough.

230
00:36:13,471 --> 00:36:17,771
lt's amazing how you still
manage to smile.

231
00:36:18,142 --> 00:36:21,771
Only a donkey in the noon sun...

232
00:36:21,913 --> 00:36:23,938
...and a poet lost in poetry
are so stunned.

233
00:36:24,315 --> 00:36:27,773
True, only the glitter of gold
is like the sun.

234
00:36:28,319 --> 00:36:30,116
So donkeys will.

235
00:36:30,321 --> 00:36:34,280
What are you talking about?
- We're discussing donkeys.

236
00:37:07,625 --> 00:37:09,593
Here l am.

237
00:37:13,631 --> 00:37:16,259
Juhi, weren't you
waiting for me?

238
00:37:17,802 --> 00:37:21,761
l'm waiting for a man in a car.
- ln a car? Not a masseur?

239
00:37:24,976 --> 00:37:26,944
May He puncture his tyres.

240
00:37:27,311 --> 00:37:29,279
May He puncture your head.

241
00:37:33,985 --> 00:37:36,954
Juhi, what happened?
- Are you cross with me?

242
00:37:37,321 --> 00:37:42,953
Have you no consideration for
the heart you've punctured?

243
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:47,290
