lf l had the gift of cheating
we could afford a car.

248
00:38:01,445 --> 00:38:03,413
l'm done for!

249
00:38:05,449 --> 00:38:08,748
A coconut? l get it.
l won't say another word.

250
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:23,757
Stop him, or l'll have to
chase him for a mile!

251
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:27,597
Stop! Naughty fellow

252
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:30,107
Hello, Pushpa.

253
00:38:31,642 --> 00:38:34,611
Vijay! l didn't recognize you.

254
00:38:35,313 --> 00:38:39,613
You were so handsome. Whose
''love'' brought you to this?

255
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:44,277
Someone who won't let me go...
Unemployment.

256
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:48,625
Your children?
- And their father's.

257
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:53,623
They're Gullu and Fullu,
bright sparks like him.

258
00:38:53,831 --> 00:38:55,799
What do you mean?

259
00:38:56,334 --> 00:39:03,968
There's a gathering at our old
college tonight; you must come.

260
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:11,141
Now l'll have to chase him
for a mile. l'll leave

261
00:39:15,686 --> 00:39:17,654
You must come tonight.

262
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:51,518
Where is Bhattacharya?
He was going to sing next.

263
00:39:59,663 --> 00:40:03,292
Vijay, why hide out here?
Come inside.

264
00:40:04,168 --> 00:40:06,295
No, Pushpa. My clothes...

265
00:40:06,504 --> 00:40:12,136
You're decently covered
from head to foot. Come along.

266
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:24,488
Ladies and gentleman.

267
00:40:24,688 --> 00:40:27,486
Bhattacharya isn't here.
We're delighted...

268
00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:31,823
...we're delighted
that Vijay is here...

269
00:40:32,029 --> 00:40:35,658
...and request him
to recite a poem.

270
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:40,000
Don't be formal. Come along.

271
00:40:58,989 --> 00:41:00,616
Let's hear you, Vijay.

272
00:41:10,501 --> 00:41:18,465
''l am weary of this
troubled life''

273
00:41:20,344 --> 00:41:28,649
''Weary of this troubled existence''

274
00:41:30,354 --> 00:41:36,156
''ln my grief, may l not
reject the entire world''

275
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:41,161
Why such a sad song on this
occasion? Recite a happy verse.

276
00:41:42,533 --> 00:41:45,161
''How can l sing of joy...''

277
00:41:45,536 --> 00:41:49,336
''if l live in pain''

278
00:41:56,814 --> 00:41:59,282
''l can only...''

279
00:41:59,483 --> 00:42:04,443
''...return to life what
life itself offers me''

280
00:42:16,166 --> 00:42:18,134
''Once again...''

281
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:22,797
''...the memories of love
stir in my heart''

282
00:42:28,679 --> 00:42:30,647
''l confess...''

283
00:42:30,781 --> 00:42:36,481
''that l am overcome
by life's blows''

284
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:51,831
''Today l break all belief...''

285
00:43:01,312 --> 00:43:05,271
''...in the illusion of hope''

286
00:43:09,987 --> 00:43:12,114
''Today l vow...''

287
00:43:12,656 --> 00:43:17,457
''to voice no complaint
against anyone''

288
00:43:44,355 --> 00:43:47,984
Are you an ex-student?

289
00:43:53,364 --> 00:43:55,264
Have you a job?

290
00:43:56,967 --> 00:43:58,935
No, l need one.

291
00:44:00,804 --> 00:44:02,772
You recite very well.

292
00:44:07,478 --> 00:44:10,447
Here's my card.
Come to my office tomorrow.

293
00:44:16,987 --> 00:44:18,955
- Yourself?
Here are my poems.

294
00:44:42,346 --> 00:44:45,804
When did you study at college?
- From '48 to '52.

295
00:44:46,350 --> 00:44:48,978
Shall l read the poems aloud?

296
00:44:55,959 --> 00:44:58,086
l married in 1952.

297
00:44:59,963 --> 00:45:01,931
Did you study science or arts?

298
00:45:03,967 --> 00:45:07,266
Arts. May l recite the poems?

299
00:45:09,139 --> 00:45:13,769
You're sure you left college
in '52, or was it before?

300
00:45:15,813 --> 00:45:21,274
ln '52. Mr. Ghosh, my poems?
- Will you work?

301
00:45:23,487 --> 00:45:29,619
Service? l thought you called me
about publishing my poems.

302
00:45:30,327 --> 00:45:33,626
There's still plenty of time
to publish your poems.

303
00:45:34,665 --> 00:45:37,133
l must get to know
you better first.

304
00:45:42,339 --> 00:45:44,967
Mr. Chatterji, this is
your new assistant.

305
00:45:46,844 --> 00:45:48,812
You can start tomorrow.

306
00:48:21,298 --> 00:48:27,259
''lf l were to give
my heart to you, only you''

307
00:48:27,804 --> 00:48:34,107
''lf l were to lock
your heart away"

308
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:15,980
''lf l were to adorn your hair
with flowers of love''

309
00:49:16,687 --> 00:49:22,648
''lf l were to shake the flowers
to the ground''

310
00:49:58,562 --> 00:50:04,626
''lf l were to remember you
in my dreams''

311
00:50:05,335 --> 00:50:11,296
''lf l were to give you
sleepless nights''

312
00:50:47,377 --> 00:50:53,338
''lf l were to lay my heart
at your feet''

313
00:50:53,817 --> 00:50:59,949
''lf l were to deny your love
and walk away"

314
00:52:54,137 --> 00:52:57,106
How have you been?
- l'm alive.

315
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:03,609
l want to see you happy.

316
00:53:03,813 --> 00:53:09,774
Don't worry. l have
learnt to be happy.

317
00:53:10,987 --> 00:53:12,955
Has some girl taught you?

318
00:53:13,990 --> 00:53:18,290
One girl was enough for me.

319
00:53:20,163 --> 00:53:22,131
l don't want to suffer again.

320
00:53:22,999 --> 00:53:26,628
You mean you have erased
your first love.

321
00:53:27,337 --> 00:53:28,634
l should have.

322
00:53:34,177 --> 00:53:38,978
l forgot: l was really going up.

323
00:54:11,982 --> 00:54:18,114
Closing time. Three hours
you've waited. For whom?

324
00:54:35,171 --> 00:54:38,299
Does Mr. Vijay come here often?

325
00:54:38,508 --> 00:54:42,308
Yes, but not lately.
Any message for him?

326
00:54:52,355 --> 00:54:56,917
So you find something to say
to the waiter. How about me?

327
00:55:03,633 --> 00:55:05,601
Have you had time
to look at them?

328
00:55:07,304 --> 00:55:10,603
- Which papers?
- Vijay calls them his poetry.

329
00:55:10,974 --> 00:55:14,273
l've read them, they're fine.

330
00:55:16,146 --> 00:55:18,114
Why not publish some?

331
00:55:19,816 --> 00:55:21,283
Are you mad?

332
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:27,446
You must know we publish famous
poets, not the trash of novices.

333
00:55:28,158 --> 00:55:30,285
Put in an advertisement instead.

334
00:55:40,003 --> 00:55:41,971
What do you want?

335
00:55:43,840 --> 00:55:46,809
Sir, this trash of a novice...

336
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:49,812
...may l take it away?

337
00:56:03,293 --> 00:56:06,751
Are you free tomorrow evening?
-

338
00:56:07,964 --> 00:56:11,092
Come and lend a hand
at a party in my house.

339
00:56:12,802 --> 00:56:14,770
l'll be there.

340
00:56:27,317 --> 00:56:29,945
lt's no good getting upset, Juhi.

341
00:56:30,153 --> 00:56:34,112
Who will care for you
in your old age?

342
00:56:34,657 --> 00:56:35,624
God willing.

343
00:56:35,759 --> 00:56:40,287
Be careful, or a nut
will fall on you.

344
00:56:40,663 --> 00:56:43,791
lf you want security,
listen to me.

345
00:56:45,502 --> 00:56:47,629
lf l listen to you, l'll starve.

346
00:56:48,838 --> 00:56:52,797
You can hardly keep yourself,
how can you feed me, too?

347
00:56:55,945 --> 00:56:59,745
My hunger will be satisfied
by seeing you in my house.

348
00:57:01,951 --> 00:57:03,919
Really?

349
00:57:04,454 --> 00:57:07,582
Abdul Sattar, do you
love me that much?

350
00:57:09,959 --> 00:57:12,757
Let's marry.
- Stop, it idiot!

351
00:57:14,631 --> 00:57:16,929
Do you hear? No, nothing.

352
00:57:20,470 --> 00:57:21,596
No nut.

353
00:57:26,810 --> 00:57:29,278
Your husband?
- He's ill.

354
00:57:29,479 --> 00:57:32,778
He wanted me to take him to
hospital, but l put it off.

355
00:57:33,149 --> 00:57:35,447
How could l miss such a party?

356
00:57:36,319 --> 00:57:38,446
You're very kind!

357
00:57:45,328 --> 00:57:47,296
And the children?

358
00:57:54,103 --> 00:57:56,071
How did you get my address?

359
00:57:56,773 --> 00:58:00,732
Your address? Do you live here?

360
00:58:01,110 --> 00:58:02,907
Let's go outside.

361
00:58:03,112 --> 00:58:06,411
Mr. Ghosh told me to come.

362
00:58:07,784 --> 00:58:11,242
Told you? Do you know him?

363
00:58:12,288 --> 00:58:14,256
l work for him.

364
00:58:15,458 --> 00:58:18,757
And you?
- l am his...

365
00:58:19,128 --> 00:58:21,926
Who is the most
talented poet here?

366
00:58:22,465 --> 00:58:24,262
They are all good.

367
00:58:24,467 --> 00:58:27,265
But the one
in the black jacket is...

368
00:58:33,977 --> 00:58:37,936
Don't tell him about us.
Understand?

369
00:58:45,321 --> 00:58:49,280
Poems that serve the nation
are better than...

370
00:58:49,425 --> 00:58:51,290
...love poems.

371
00:58:51,995 --> 00:58:54,463
Gentleman, drop this argument.

372
00:58:55,665 --> 00:58:57,792
The drinks are here.

373
00:59:00,837 --> 00:59:03,135
Leave it to the servant, dear.

374
00:59:05,341 --> 00:59:08,640
Come along, serve the drinks.

375
00:59:20,423 --> 00:59:23,824
''How could l...''

376
00:59:24,360 --> 00:59:27,659
''apprise her of my love?''

377
00:59:28,364 --> 00:59:31,492
''The words froze on my lips''

378
00:59:32,035 --> 00:59:35,004
''Tears welled in my eyes''

379
00:59:37,106 --> 00:59:40,007
''ln the gallantry
of frigid hearts''

380
00:59:40,543 --> 00:59:43,842
''Where pleasure is sought''

381
00:59:44,614 --> 00:59:47,515
''Clammy fingers cling
to the cup of whine''

382
00:59:48,051 --> 00:59:51,020
''l quaffed the wine,
a drop was spilled''

383
01:00:01,497 --> 01:00:06,628
''An extreme despair
came to my rescue''

384
01:00:07,770 --> 01:00:12,969
''Receiving my poet, out of pity,
she deigned to love me''

385
01:00:19,182 --> 01:00:25,485
''Who are the fortunate ones...''

386
01:00:26,689 --> 01:00:29,658
''who gain the love they seek?''

387
01:00:32,528 --> 01:00:37,488
Great, Mr Ghosh!
Even your servants recite poems

388
01:00:39,369 --> 01:00:41,337
l'll arrange for the dinner
Can only the rich be poets?

389
01:00:45,708 --> 01:00:48,506
Go ahead, young man

390
01:01:01,491 --> 01:01:09,125
''When l asked for flowers,
l was given thorns''

391
01:01:11,768 --> 01:01:16,296
''Who are the fortunate ones...''

392
01:01:16,506 --> 01:01:19,304
''who gain the love they seek?''

393
01:01:29,352 --> 01:01:33,652
''When l searched for happiness...''

394
01:01:34,023 --> 01:01:36,992
''l was lost in streets
of sadness''

395
01:01:49,372 --> 01:01:56,938
''When l sought songs of joy,
l heard songs of sorrow"

396
01:01:58,981 --> 01:02:06,945
''Every torment doubled
the pain my heart''

397
01:02:09,158 --> 01:02:16,963
''When l asked for flowers,
l was given thorns''

398
01:02:19,335 --> 01:02:23,795
''Who were the fortunate ones...''

399
01:02:24,173 --> 01:02:26,971
''who got the love they sought''

400
01:02:36,786 --> 01:02:42,986
''Companions came...''

401
01:02:46,562 --> 01:02:54,264
''Companions came, stayed awhile,
then left me all alone''

402
01:02:56,472 --> 01:03:04,436
''Who can spare the time to clasp
the hand of a falling man?''

403
01:03:06,315 --> 01:03:13,949
''Even my shadow eludes me
as it fades away"

404
01:03:16,425 --> 01:03:24,127
''When l asked for flowers,
l was given thorns''

405
01:03:26,335 --> 01:03:33,969
''Who are the fortunate ones
who gain the love they seek?''

406
01:03:43,853 --> 01:03:51,487
''lf this is called living,
then l'll live my life somehow"

407
01:04:03,973 --> 01:04:11,436
''l shall not sigh, l'll seal my lips,
l'll dry my tears''

408
01:04:13,649 --> 01:04:21,283
''Why should l fear grief,
when l have encountered it so often?''

409
01:04:23,492 --> 01:04:31,297
''When l asked for flowers,
l was given thorns''

410
01:04:33,336 --> 01:04:41,141
''Who are the fortunate ones
who gain the love they seek?''

411
01:04:44,780 --> 01:04:46,748
Wonderful! Excellent!

412
01:05:15,311 --> 01:05:17,279
l have come to see you.

413
01:05:25,321 --> 01:05:28,449
Mr. Ghosh has gone
to the board meeting.

414
01:05:30,326 --> 01:05:32,294
You shouldn't have come.

415
01:05:36,832 --> 01:05:39,960
l have been very upset
since the party.

416
01:05:41,671 --> 01:05:43,639
Do you bear me ill will?

417
01:05:44,340 --> 01:05:48,470
No, Meena.
l bear no grudge.

418
01:05:54,951 --> 01:05:59,081
Why did you sing that
heart-rending poem that day?

419
01:06:04,961 --> 01:06:09,091
You revived my desires.
- Forget the past.

420
01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:17,094
l had forgotten,
l had remoulded my life.

421
01:06:18,140 --> 01:06:20,108
l controlled my heart.

422
01:06:23,646 --> 01:06:27,275
Why disturb my heart?
Why return to my life?

423
01:06:28,150 --> 01:06:33,281
When did l ever leave
your life? You left me.

424
01:06:34,323 --> 01:06:41,126
Do not try to correct your first
mistake with another, Meena.

425
01:06:41,664 --> 01:06:43,632
l've made no mistake.

426
01:06:44,166 --> 01:06:48,796
Besides love, a sensible woman needs
security and the comfort of a home.

427
01:06:49,338 --> 01:06:51,465
And some money is also required.

428
01:06:53,509 --> 01:06:55,067
For those things...

429
01:06:55,277 --> 01:07:00,579
You married Mr. Ghosh,
selling love for wealth.

430
01:07:00,950 --> 01:07:02,918
Don't accuse me wrongly.

431
01:07:04,954 --> 01:07:09,254
l loved you, but you
were poor and unemployed.

432
01:07:10,126 --> 01:07:14,586
ln life, besides love
and poetry, there's hunger.

433
01:07:15,297 --> 01:07:19,927
How could you bear my burden
when you couldn't feed yourself?

434
01:07:20,636 --> 01:07:22,604
You gave me no chance.

435
01:07:23,305 --> 01:07:27,435
When a man has responsibilities,
he shoulders them.

436
01:07:27,977 --> 01:07:29,945
Don't deceive yourself.

437
01:07:30,479 --> 01:07:35,781
You sought wealth and
high position in society.

438
01:07:36,318 --> 01:07:40,778
Now you have them. Despite that,
you are restless and resentful.

439
01:07:40,990 --> 01:07:42,958
You know why?

440
01:07:43,993 --> 01:07:46,621
Because you have always
been selfish.

441
01:07:48,497 --> 01:07:51,125
You never considered my plight.

442
01:07:52,668 --> 01:07:56,229
Now you don't
consider your husband.

443
01:08:01,777 --> 01:08:07,238
Life's real joy lies
in making others happy.

444
01:08:08,284 --> 01:08:12,914
You've never understood that;
that's why you're unhappy.

445
01:08:26,635 --> 01:08:28,102
Wonderful!

446
01:08:28,304 --> 01:08:30,932
My wife's no better
than a streetwalker.

447
01:08:31,140 --> 01:08:34,439
Vijay and l hardly know each other.

448
01:08:34,643 --> 01:08:36,770
How long has this been going on?

449
01:08:36,912 --> 01:08:38,880
We hardly know each other.

450
01:08:39,048 --> 01:08:41,016
Anything else?
- Nothing.

451
01:08:42,318 --> 01:08:47,620
Then let's see how upset you are
when l dismiss him.

452
01:09:02,671 --> 01:09:06,300
Pay up!
- l earn my money the hard way.

453
01:09:06,675 --> 01:09:08,643
Scoundrel! Pay Up!

454
01:09:10,579 --> 01:09:12,137
Constable!

455
01:09:57,993 --> 01:09:59,961
Save me, do something!

456
01:10:02,498 --> 01:10:03,965
You?

457
01:10:05,000 --> 01:10:06,968
What's the matter?

458
01:10:10,005 --> 01:10:11,973
Has a girl run this way?

459
01:10:13,008 --> 01:10:14,305
No.

460
01:10:14,510 --> 01:10:18,469
Who is she?
- My wife.

461
01:10:21,850 --> 01:10:23,977
Sorry sir, l made a mistake.

462
01:10:27,690 --> 01:10:29,658
What is your name?

463
01:10:33,195 --> 01:10:34,492
Gulab.

464
01:10:35,197 --> 01:10:38,997
lt's all clear now.
You can go safely.

465
01:11:06,495 --> 01:11:13,628
''Tormented by a long absence...''

466
01:11:16,505 --> 01:11:18,473
''Radha longed...''

467
01:11:22,177 --> 01:11:25,635
''for her lover''

468
01:11:27,516 --> 01:11:35,821
''One day she went...''

469
01:11:40,362 --> 01:11:44,992
''to her beloved and lamented''

470
01:11:52,041 --> 01:11:56,944
''Hold me in your arms
today, my love...''

471
01:11:57,146 --> 01:12:00,115
''so that l am fulfilled''

472
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:15,958
''Ease the pain in my heart...''

473
01:12:16,498 --> 01:12:19,956
''slake the fire in my body"

474
01:12:50,532 --> 01:12:52,659
''My eyes are wide open''

475
01:12:54,636 --> 01:12:57,264
''My luckless eyes''

476
01:13:03,645 --> 01:13:07,445
''l can't rest until
l am truly yours''

477
01:13:13,055 --> 01:13:16,957
''l can hardly see ahead.
Behind me torment follows''

478
01:13:17,326 --> 01:13:21,285
''Without you,
life is meaningless''

479
01:13:22,331 --> 01:13:28,292
''Beloved, make my love complete''

480
01:13:37,346 --> 01:13:44,809
''so it may last
''Call me your very own''

481
01:14:13,315 --> 01:14:17,945
''Call me your own,
''Slake the thirst...''

